<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<cheatsheet
      title="Invoke the Hello World Service">
   <intro>
      <description>
         The Web Services Explorer generates a SOAP request that drives the Hello World service.
      </description>
   </intro>
   <item
         title="Start the Web Services Explorer">
      <description>
         Right click <b>upgrade.helloworld.soa/Service Descriptors/HelloWorld_gen.wsdl</b> and select <b>Web Services &gt; Test with Web Services Explorer</b>. The WSDL file opens in the Web Service Explorer.
      </description>
   </item>
   <item
         title="Generate a sayHello Request">
      <description>
         In the Navigator pane, expand the <b>HelloWorldSOAP</b> node.<br/><br/>

Click the <b>sayHello</b> node.<br/><br/>

In the Invoke a WSDL Operation pane on the right, type <b>Jim</b> in the HelloRequest field. Click <b>Go</b>. The Status pane displays:<br/><br/>
 HelloResponse (string):  Hi Jim! This is the Java component.
      </description>
   </item>
</cheatsheet>
